%sql
select * from 
    (select address_, max(sale_price) as max_sale_price, count(address_) as N_transactions,
        to_number(max(XCoord)) as xcoord, to_number(max(YCoord)) as ycoord
        from admin.brooklyn_sales_map 
        where BUILDING_CLASS_CATEGORY in ('02 TWO FAMILY HOMES', '01 ONE FAMILY HOMES')
        group by address_)
    where (rownum < 7);

paragraphs.text:
%python
query = """
select * from 
    (select address_, max(sale_price) as max_sale_price, avg(to_number(xcoord)) as xcoord, avg(to_number(ycoord)) as ycoord, 
        count(address_) as N_transactions from 
            (select address_, sale_price, xcoord, ycoord, BUILDING_CLASS_CATEGORY from admin.brooklyn_sales_map 
                where (XCOORD != 'NA') and (YCOORD != 'NA') and BUILDING_CLASS_CATEGORY in ('02 TWO FAMILY HOMES', '01 ONE FAMILY HOMES'))
        group by address_
    ) where (xcoord > 123456) and (ycoord > 123456)
"""
proxy = oml.sync(query=query)
print ('proxy.shape = ', proxy.shape)
xy = proxy
xy.head()

paragraphs.title: compute relative lat, long
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = geolocate_train
delta_latitute = proxy['latitute'] - latitute_ref
proxy = proxy.concat({'delta_latitute':delta_latitute})
delta_longitude = proxy['longitude'] - longitude_ref
proxy = proxy.concat({'delta_longitude':delta_longitude})
geolocate_train = proxy
geolocate_train

paragraphs.title: merge xy_relative and geolocate_train to get training data
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = xy_relative.merge(geolocate_train, on='ADDRESS_', how='inner', suffixes=('', ''))
proxy = proxy[['ADDRESS_', 'delta_XCOORD', 'delta_YCOORD', 'delta_latitute', 'delta_longitude']]
train = proxy
train

paragraphs.title: train regression model to estimate delta_latitute
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = train
case_id = 'ADDRESS_'
target = 'delta_latitute'
model_name = 'DELTA_LATITUDE_MODEL'
x_cols = [case_id, 'delta_XCOORD', 'delta_YCOORD']
X = proxy[x_cols]
Y = proxy[target]
settings = {}
try:
    oml.drop(model=model_name)
except:
    print('No such model')
model = oml.glm("regression", **settings)
model = model.fit(X, Y, model_name=model_name, case_id=case_id)
delta_latitute_model = model

%python
train

paragraphs.title: train model to estimate delta_longitude
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = train
case_id = 'ADDRESS_'
target = 'delta_longitude'
model_name = 'DELTA_LONGITUDE_MODEL'
X = proxy[x_cols]
Y = proxy[target]
try:
    oml.drop(model=model_name)
except:
    print('No such model')
model = oml.glm("regression", **settings)
model = model.fit(X, Y, model_name=model_name, case_id=case_id)
delta_longitude_model = model

paragraphs.title: use delta_latitute_model to estimate each address's latitude
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = xy_relative
model = delta_latitute_model
X = proxy[x_cols]
proxy = model.predict(X, supplemental_cols=proxy)
proxy = proxy.rename({'PREDICTION':'delta_latitute'})
latitude_ = proxy['delta_latitute'] + latitute_ref
proxy = proxy.concat({'LATITUDE_':latitude_})
latitude = proxy
print ('latitude.shape = ', latitude.shape)
latitude.head()

paragraphs.title: use delta_longitude_model to estimate each address's longitude
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = xy_relative
model = delta_longitude_model
cols = [case_id] + x_cols
X = proxy[cols]
proxy = model.predict(X, supplemental_cols=proxy[case_id])
proxy = proxy.rename({'PREDICTION':'delta_longitude'})
longitude_ = proxy['delta_longitude'] + longitude_ref
proxy = proxy.concat({'LONGITUDE_':longitude_})
proxy = proxy[['ADDRESS_', 'LONGITUDE_']]
lat_long = latitude.merge(proxy, on='ADDRESS_', how='inner', suffixes=('', ''))
lat_long.head()

paragraphs.title: write lat_long to ADW table
paragraphs.text:
%python
proxy = lat_long
proxy = proxy[['ADDRESS_', 'MAX_SALE_PRICE', 'N_TRANSACTIONS', 'LATITUDE_', 'LONGITUDE_']]
table = 'BROOKLYN_LAT_LONG'
try:
    oml.drop(table)
except:
    pass
print ('proxy.shape = ', proxy.shape)
proxy = proxy.materialize(table=table)
proxy.head()
